  <prompt>
    Document that this project uses the **operator-only approval model** per revised NFR-08 (2026-05-24). UQ-01 ("Who is the dual approver?") is resolved: there is no dual approver. Verification rigor for MEDIUM/HIGH-tier candidates (Phase 4) and Phase 5 promotions comes from:

    1. **AI-directed checks** — `task-execute` skill's mandatory `adr-check` + `code-review` gates at Step 9.5 (FULL rigor)
    2. **CI guards** — FR-C1 through FR-C6 (non-Linux RID, sourcemaps, vuln transitives, oversize publish, direct AI injection)
    3. **Owner judgment** — sign-off authority

    This task replaces the original "designate a second human approver" — the dual-approver enterprise pattern is explicitly NOT used for this project. Rationale: single project owner + AI-directed coding procedures provide effective check-and-balance without the friction of a second human approver.
  </prompt>

  <role>Project owner.</role>

  <goal>
    Operator-only approval model documented in `CLAUDE.md → Decisions Made`. UQ-01 marked RESOLVED.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="ai-spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md (NFR-08 revised + UQ-01 resolution)</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-08 revised 2026-05-24">Owner sign-off + AI-directed verification model; dual-approver enterprise pattern NOT used</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md UQ-01 RESOLVED 2026-05-24">Operator-only model adopted</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Originally, design.md §3 added "dual approver required for MEDIUM/HIGH tier candidates" to mitigate sole-approver risk — a concern that makes sense when multiple humans share codebase ownership. For Spaarke's actual operating model (single project owner + AI-directed coding procedures), the dual-approver pattern adds friction without proportional benefit.

      The AI-directed checks (adr-check, code-review at task-execute Step 9.5) provide the "second pair of eyes" doing technical verification. The owner provides judgment + sign-off. Combined with FR-C1–C6 CI guards (mechanical enforcement), the verification rigor is preserved without a second human approver bottleneck.

      Senior review 2026-05-24 confirmed: with FR-C6 (new direct-AI-injection CI gate) added and existing CI guards enforced, all MEDIUM/HIGH-tier risk surfaces have mechanical or AI-directed gates.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">Owner sign-off must complete first</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Record decision in `CLAUDE.md → Decisions Made` (entry already added 2026-05-24 — verify present)</step>
    <step order="2">Confirm spec.md NFR-08 (revised) and UQ-01 (RESOLVED) reflect this decision</step>
    <step order="3">Confirm no remaining task POMLs require "dual approver ACK" — verify task 054, 060, 062 use revised language</step>
    <step order="4">Update Phase 0 checklist item 6 to checked with note: "Operator-only model — UQ-01 resolved 2026-05-24"</step>
    <step order="5">Update TASK-INDEX.md status of task 002 from 🔲 to ✅</step>
  </steps>

